# Production Environment Setup Script

This script helps you set up environment variables for production deployment.

## Usage:

1. Copy this template to your server
2. Run: `source setup-prod-env.sh`
3. Set your values
4. Export to your deployment platform

## Variables:

# Database (PostgreSQL Production)
export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:5432/influencerhub_prod"

# JWT Secrets (Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32)
export JWT_SECRET="<generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32>"
export JWT_REFRESH_SECRET="<generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32>"

# Token Expiry
export JWT_EXPIRY="15m"
export JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY="7d"

# Server
export PORT="5001"
export NODE_ENV="production"

# CORS - Your production domains
export ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://app.influencerhub.com,https://www.influencerhub.com"

# Frontend API URL
export VITE_API_URL="https://api.influencerhub.com/api/v1"

## For Heroku:

```bash
heroku config:set DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..." --app influencerhub-api
heroku config:set JWT_SECRET="..." --app influencerhub-api
heroku config:set JWT_REFRESH_SECRET="..." --app influencerhub-api
heroku config:set NODE_ENV=production --app influencerhub-api
heroku config:set ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://app.influencerhub.com" --app influencerhub-api
```

## For Railway:

Set in Railway dashboard:
- DATABASE_URL
- JWT_SECRET
- JWT_REFRESH_SECRET
- NODE_ENV=production
- ALLOWED_ORIGINS

## For Docker Compose:

```bash
docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
```

## For AWS Lambda / Serverless:

Set environment variables in serverless.yml or AWS console:
- All of the above environment variables
- Plus: LAMBDA_TASK_ROOT, PATH, etc. (handled by AWS)

## Security Notes:

- Never commit .env files to git
- Use strong, randomly generated secrets
- Rotate secrets every 90 days
- Never share secrets in communication
- Use secure vaults (AWS Secrets Manager, Vault, etc.)
- Enable audit logging for secret access
